{% doc %}
  @prompt
    Full-width rectangular hero block with rounded corners.
    
    Left side: background image or gradient overlay with optional category/tag labels.
    
    Right side: secondary image (or graphic element, like a person/cloud).
    
    Bottom overlay: dark gradient background for text readability.
    
    Customizable Options in Theme Editor (Schema Settings):
    
    Section Title (text) → Default: blog article headline.
    
    Subtitle / Excerpt (richtext) → short supporting text.
    
    Category (text) → e.g., “Women” with breadcrumb-style link.
    
    Subcategory (text/link) → e.g., “Hormonal Health”.
    
    Reading Time (text) → e.g., “5 min read”.
    
    Tag Labels (multi-text) → e.g., “Wellness”, “Health”.
    
    Primary Image (image_picker) → background/left image.
    
    Secondary Image (image_picker) → right-side visual (like a person/cloud).
    
    Overlay Color (color_picker) → gradient overlay on background.
    
    Headline Text Color (color_picker).
    
    Tag Background & Text Color (color_picker).
    
    Article Link (url) → click-through to full blog article.
    
    Design & Styling:
    
    Rounded corners (border-radius: 16px).
    
    Responsive grid: left image/content, right image.
    
    On mobile: stack vertically (image on top, text below).
    
    Smooth hover effect (slight zoom on image).
    
    Tag labels styled as pill-shaped buttons.
    
    Default Content Example:
    
    Category: Women > Hormonal Health
    
